cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper discusses an information-theoretic framework to compare different transmission/detection strategies by computing the information rate of the user in the reference beam.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the achievable rates by a single user in multibeam satellite scenarios.
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) is another possible category as the paper discusses the transmission and detection strategies in multibeam satellite systems.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the performance of different detection strategies in satellite systems.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on algorithms or data structures, but rather on the performance of different detection strategies in satellite systems.
